HEADWORD: moorhen
<hw>moorhen</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
black gallinule (<spn>Gallinula chloropus</spn>) that inhabits ponds and
lakes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Gallinula chloropus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The female of the <er>moor fowl</er>; the
<altname>moor hen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mooring</ent>⟦br⟧
